## Overview

The UX team in the [Verify:Runner Group](/handbook/engineering/development/ops/verify/runner/) is responsible for Runner SaaS and Runner self-managed. We are focused on supporting the [Runner JTBDs](/handbook/engineering/development/ops/verify/runner/jtbd/) by understanding what users are struggling with, solving for those problems, and improving the overall experience to make it easy as possible to use runners and CI/CD.

We measure our success through a combination of experience scores, through [SUS evaluations](/engineering/ux/performance-indicators/system-usability-scale) of the GitLab product, [UX scorecards](/handbook/product/ux/ux-scorecards/) and [Category Maturity scorecards](/handbook/product/ux/category-maturity-scorecards/) and usage metrics (we are in progress of integrating and making use of these more often). Our goal is to provide the easiest feature set to manage, use and "not have to worry about" runners.

## Runner fleet UX vision

[Platform engineers](/product/personas/#priyanka-platform-engineer) struggle managing large fleets of runners today. They are not equipped with enough configuration capabilities to manage and administer the fleet. This negatively impacts their teams as they sometimes end up running into blockers when using the runners. We have captured many issues, including customer requests and [FY22-Q3 UX scorecard recommendations](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab-design/-/issues/1666), in the [Runner fleet meta epic](https://gitlab.com/groups/gitlab-org/-/epics/7475) that further document this problem and how we plan to solve it.

The vision for this problem is to provide users with a flexibile set of management capabilities to troubleshoot quickly and support their teams. To do this, we've broken down the vision into:
  - [Search and attribution](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/343810): Visionary features to enhance the search and filter capabilities in the Admin runners UI to, for example, view all runners assigned to a single project. We would like to use this as a foundation to include automation in the future as well, such as, stale runner garbage collection. Watch the [summary video](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8nSos4pbMng) for the full vision, including mockups.
  - [CI/CD job queues](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/345594): Visionary features to provide more insight into the job queues of a runner, which is important when identifying why runners are not working as expected, as well as to prevent overloaded runners. This vision is in progress.

